@page "/vr-prototype-2d"
@using SpawnDev.BlazorJS
@using SpawnDev.VoxelEngine.Rendering

<PageTitle>VR Prototype (2D measurement)</PageTitle>

<h3>VR Prototype - 2D measurement rig (Phase VR.1a)</h3>

<p>
    This page measures whether the hybrid fallback render path can hit a 90 fps VR budget on Quest 3S native browser.
    Runs the same scene through two render paths side-by-side, logs per-frame timing, and reports the answer.
</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Path A (direct):</strong> WebGPU compute shader writes animated gradient to a GPUTexture; WebGPU renders that texture to a canvas via <code>GPUCanvasContext</code>.</li>
    <li><strong>Path B (hybrid):</strong> Same compute output, rendered to an <code>OffscreenCanvas</code> via WebGPU, then <code>transferToImageBitmap()</code> + <code>WebGL2.texImage2D(imageBitmap)</code> + WebGL2 draws a full-screen quad to a canvas.</li>
</ul>

<p style="color:#facc15;">
    <strong>Status:</strong> Placeholder. Measurement pipeline shipping in the next commit.
    <br />
    Current render path reported by the probe:
    @if (_report != null)
    {
        <code style="color:@PathColor(_report.Path)">@_report.Path</code>
    }
    else
    {
        <em>probing...</em>
    }
</p>

<p style="color:#888;font-size:0.9em;">
    If you land here before the measurement code ships, visit <a href="render-path">/render-path</a>
    to see the full capability report. The measurement will branch behavior based on the detected path:
    FullWebGpu skips the WebGL2 bridge entirely (native primary path); HybridWebGl2 measures the bridge overhead
    head-to-head against the direct path; WebGpuOnly runs desktop 2D for dev iteration.
</p>

@inject BlazorJSRuntime JS

@code {
    RenderPathReport? _report;

    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        _report = await RenderPathDetector.DetectAsync(JS);
    }

    static string PathColor(RenderPath p) => p switch
    {
        RenderPath.FullWebGpu => "#4ade80",
        RenderPath.HybridWebGl2 => "#facc15",
        RenderPath.WebGpuOnly => "#60a5fa",
        RenderPath.None => "#ef4444",
        _ => "#888",
    };
}
